comment.author: 34586311@N05
comment._content: From the Newport Chamber of Commerce: Yaquina Bay Road ends at Toledo, once the location of the world's largest spruce mill, built by the U.S. Government to provide spruce for airplane manufacture in World War I and which later provided all of the wood that went into Howard Hughes' infamous Spruce Goose."
